25|$|The Women's International Auxiliary {{was formed}} at the 1902 Cincinnati ITU Convention. The WIA slogan was Spend Union Earned Money for Union Label Products and Union Services and its {{quarterly}} publication was Label Facts. The WIA {{contributed to the}} Union Printers Home Fund with various fund raising events. At each ITU convention the WIA would award prizes for the, Union Label Poster contest. Only printer <b>wives</b> <b>were</b> eligible to be elected to the WIA local and international offices. After 1948, mailers' <b>wives</b> <b>were</b> only eligible to serve the local and international WIA auxiliary as third vice president.|$|E
