50|$|The Persian {{historian}} Muhammad ibn Jarir al-Tabari (c. 915) recounts that Japheth's <b>wife</b> <b>was</b> Arbasisah, {{daughter of}} Marazil, son of al-Darmasil, son of Mehujael, son of Enoch, son of Cain; that Ham's <b>wife</b> <b>was</b> Naḥlab, daughter of Marib, another son of al-Darmasil; and that Shem's <b>wife</b> <b>was</b> Ṣalib, daughter of Batawil, another son of Mehujael. He says Noah's <b>wife</b> <b>was</b> Amzurah, daughter of Barakil, another son of Mehujael.|$|R
